<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="431" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,979,1399]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,438,979,1004]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">Comparative diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[578,763,979,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Helcon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcatus">
<emphasis box="[578,763,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">Helcon sulcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(length of fore wing 
<quantity box="[1028,1123,979,1003]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="4.0">4-9 mm</quantity>
, antennal segments 34-37, antenna brown apically; hind femur somewhat narrowed subapically and length of ovipositor sheath about 1.1 times fore wing), but has first metasomal tergite evenly widened posteriorly and about as long as its apical width (hardly widened and about 1.4 times longer than its apical width in 
<taxonomicName box="[915,1041,1086,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Helcon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcatus">
<emphasis box="[915,1041,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">H. sulcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and hind femur rather robust (fig. 
<quantity box="[151,208,1123,1148]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.906" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" unit="in" value="39.0">39 in</quantity>
van 
<bibRefCitation author="Achterberg" box="[262,457,1123,1148]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" refString="van Achterberg, C. (1987) Revision of the European Helconini (Hymenoptera, Braconidae, Helconinae). Zoologische Mededelingen, Leiden, 61, 263 - 285." type="journal article" year="1987">Achterberg, 1987</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis box="[464,487,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">vs</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[495,560,1123,1148]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,700,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[340,1247,700,1874]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Helcon sulcatus sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, fore wing; B, hind wing; C, mesosoma, lateral aspect; D, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; E, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; F, habitus, lateral aspect; G, head, lateral aspect; H, head, dorsal aspect; I, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827534/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
E of 
<taxonomicName box="[614,741,1123,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Helcon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcatus">
<emphasis box="[614,741,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">H. sulcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
