<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="431" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,979,1399]" box="[199,707,1195,1220]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1195,1220]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe, 
<collectingCountry box="[454,502,1196,1219]" name="Iran" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">Iran</collectingCountry>
,? 
<collectingCountry box="[523,592,1195,1220]" name="China" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[607,704,1195,1220]" country="China" name="Taiwan)" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">
<collectingCountry box="[607,695,1195,1220]" name="Taiwan" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
)
</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,979,1399]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1572323485" collectorName="van Achterberg" country="China" location="West Palaearctic" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" specimenCount="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1230,1255]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">Notes.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Chou" box="[440,660,1230,1255]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" refString="Chou, L. Y. &amp; Hsu, T. C. (1998) The Braconidae (Hymenoptera) of Taiwan 8. Brulleiini, Diospilini and Helconini. Journal of Agricultural Research of China, 47 (3), 283 - 314." type="journal article" year="1998">
Chou et 
<bibRefCitation author="Hsu" box="[539,660,1231,1255]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" refString="Chou, L. Y. &amp; Hsu, T. C. (1998) The Braconidae (Hymenoptera) of Taiwan 8. Brulleiini, Diospilini and Helconini. Journal of Agricultural Research of China, 47 (3), 283 - 314." type="journal article" year="1998">Hsu (1998</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 83) the hind femur has a “wide protuberance subapically”, but according to 
<collectorName box="[296,468,1267,1292]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">
van 
<bibRefCitation author="Achterberg" box="[343,468,1267,1292]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" refString="van Achterberg, C. (1987) Revision of the European Helconini (Hymenoptera, Braconidae, Helconinae). Zoologische Mededelingen, Leiden, 61, 263 - 285." type="journal article" year="1987">Achterberg</bibRefCitation>
</collectorName>
(1987) the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:ED2587DDFFAFFFE346D7FCA7921AFACE:60536010FFAFFFE34415FB1A9026FAB5" box="[597,781,1267,1292]" country="China" name="West Palaearctic" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">West Palaearctic</location>
<taxonomicName box="[788,953,1267,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Helcon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claviventris">
<emphasis box="[788,953,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">W. claviventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a small ventral protuberance (fig. 
<quantity box="[1379,1436,1267,1292]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.906" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" unit="in" value="39.0">39 in</quantity>
<collectorName box="[151,329,1302,1327]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">
van 
<bibRefCitation author="Achterberg" box="[201,329,1302,1327]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" refString="van Achterberg, C. (1987) Revision of the European Helconini (Hymenoptera, Braconidae, Helconinae). Zoologische Mededelingen, Leiden, 61, 263 - 285." type="journal article" year="1987">Achterberg</bibRefCitation>
</collectorName>
, 1987) resulting in a somewhat widened femur. It may concern an undescribed species and the occurrence of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[473,540,1339,1364]" name="China" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">China</collectingCountry>
is uncertain. This species belongs to the redefined genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Cameron" authorityName="Cameron" box="[1181,1436,1339,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Wroughtonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1181,1326,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">Wroughtonia</emphasis>
Cameron
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,288,1374,1399]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">comb. nov.</emphasis>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
